        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 8:47PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 847 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Nebo, or near Ceres, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Bland...
Marion...
Rural Retreat...
Ceres...
Max Meadows...
and Mount Rogers National Recreation Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
